\b\fs24 Summary of Findings\b0\fs22\par
\par
Following a comprehensive internal investigation and review of body camera footage, witness statements, and forensic evidence, the Internal Affairs Division has concluded that Officer Michael Brown violated department policy and state law regarding the use of force. Specifically, Officer Brown employed excessive and unnecessary force during the arrest of Mr. Jamal Williams on March 15, 2024. The investigation determined that Officer Brown's actions, including the use of a chokehold after the subject had been subdued, constituted misconduct. As a result, Officer Michael Brown was found guilty of excessive force and misconduct in this police brutality case, leading to his immediate suspension and pending termination. This finding has been forwarded to the District Attorney's office for potential criminal charges.\par
